    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I think we could/should convert the `fn(..., true, false, false)` into\r\n`fn(..., {verifyStateRoot: true, verifyProposer: true, verifySignatures: true})`\r\n\r\nI don't think the above `BlockSignatureStrategy` behavior should be handled by our `lodestar-beacon-state-transition` code, but rather by the direct consumer, eg: a [`ChainProcessor`](https://hackmd.io/jS7QMXR2Q4Os-JS-ZFHBAQ?view#Chain-Processor) module. We would be able to determine the signature strategy based on the \"job\" metadata and whether the processor receives a single block or a chain segment.",
